        "id": 1087048
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-01T18:19:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Doesn\u0027t that mean the logic should be\n(port !\u003d 0 || mode !\u003d kIPv4AndIPv6)\nor\n(port \u003d\u003d 0 \u0026\u0026 mode \u003d\u003d kIPv4AndIPv6) with reverted ternary arguments.\nAs it is now it will do 5 tries if port \u003d\u003d 0 and you only want IPv4. Or am I missing something?",
      "parentUuid": "0e06dc0a_2558b403",
